          "type": "reasoning",
          "text": "The user is asking what I mean by \"тяжёлая функция для вещественной степени\" (heavy function for real exponent).\n\n`pow(x, 2)` computes `x` raised to the power of 2 using floating-point exponentiation (logarithms + exponentiation internally). This is much more computationally expensive than `x * x`, which is a single multiplication instruction on the CPU.\n\nFor x^2, `x*x` is:\n- Faster (one CPU instruction vs dozens for log+exp)\n- More precise (no floating-point rounding from the algorithm)\n- More idiomatic in C\n\n`pow` should be used when the exponent is non-integer or a variable, not for small constant integers.",
